title: Matchsafe, "The White House, Washington, D.C.", 1900–10
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: Rectangular, curved top and bottom, featuring horizontal, sepia-toned, photographic image of the White House, inscribed below "White House, Washington D.C.", reverse features horizontal, sepia-toned and hand colored photographic image of the Capital, inscribed below "The Capital, Washington, D.C.", side panel beneath White House image inscribed "Washington, D.C." Lid hinged on side. Striker on bottom.

tombstone.epitaph:
Matchsafe, "The White House, Washington, D.C.", 1900–10.
1900–10. Plated metal, printed celluloid. Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener. 1980-14-640.
